generate keystore:
"c:\Program Files\Java\jre1.8.0_191\bin\keytool" -genkeypair -keysize 2048 -keyalg RSA -alias "Test Docker" -storetype jks -keystore test_docker.jks -ext san=ip:127.0.0.1,ip:192.168.99.100,ip:192.168.99.101,ip:172.17.0.1,dns:localhost -storepass changeit
add first and last name
other options by default
in keystoreexplorer export PEM certificate and private key (do not encrypt)

second variant to to generate keystore
"c:\Program Files\Java\jre1.8.0_181\bin\keytool" -genkeypair -keysize 2048 -keyalg RSA -dname "CN=test-docker" -alias "Test Docker" -storetype PKCS12 -keystore test_docker.jks -ext san=ip:127.0.0.1,ip:192.168.99.100,ip:192.168.99.101,dns:localhost -storepass changeit -keypass changeit
export key and certificate:
"c:\Program Files\Java\jre1.8.0_191\bin\keytool" -export -keystore test_docker.jks -alias "Test Docker" -file test_docker.cer -storepass changeit
in git-bash (winpty for windows):
winpty openssl pkcs12 -in test_docker.p12 -out server.key -passin pass:changeit -nocerts -nodes
winpty openssl pkcs8 -out test_docker.key -in server.key -nocrypt

